{{No footnotes|date=April 2010}} {{Infobox person | name = Ken Weatherwax | image = | caption = | birth_name = Kenneth Patrick Weatherwax | birth_place = [[Los Angeles|Los Angeles, California]], [[United States|U.S.]] | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1955|9|29}} | occupation = Actor | spouse = | yearsactive = 1964âpresent }} '''Kenneth Patrick "Ken" Weatherwax''' (born September 29, 1955 in [[Los Angeles|Los Angeles, California]]) is an [[United States|American]] actor, best known for playing [[Pugsley Addams]] on ''[[The Addams Family (TV series)|The Addams Family]]'' television series.
After ''The Addams Family'' was canceled, Weatherwax found it difficult to get work in Hollywood (a common occurrence for [[child actor]]s) and was typecast as Pugsley well into his teens. At 17, Weatherwax entered the [[United States Army|U.S. Army]] with his only childhood friend, Adam Knowles. He makes appearances at conventions and still offers his services for acting jobs ranging from [[voice-over]]s to personal appearances.
Ken Weatherwax has been working behind the camera as a movie studio [[grip (job)|grip]] for a number of years. Said to have worked as a set builder on movie lots 1992-2002.
==Family members in film and TV== His aunt was [[Ruby Keeler]].<ref name="Lamparski">{{cite book|title=Whatever Became Of ...? Eighth Series|last=Lamparski|first=Richard|authorlink=|coauthors=|year=1982|publisher=Crown Publishers|location=New York|isbn=0-517-54855-0|page=|pages=230â231|url=|accessdate=}}</ref> His brother is [[Joey D. Vieira]], also known as Donald Keeler, who played "Porky" on the first three seasons of TV's ''[[Lassie (1954 TV series)|Lassie]]'', beginning in 1954.<ref name="Lamparski" />
